title: Researching a Chicago Building
copy: Starting Points: From the Commission on Chicago Landmarks Your House Has a History: A Step-by-Step Guide to Researching Your Property A clear and concise step-by-step guide to researching your home. Chicago Historic Resources Survey: An Inventory of Architecturally and Historically Significant Structures City of Chicago website that includes maps, an architectural style guide, a database of architecturally and historically significant structures, landmark status of each listed building, and an extensive bibliography.
